OL,3,CDriver left with #1,500 bill after
OL,4,Cpotholes damage wheels
OL,6,FA driver said he has had to fork out
OL,7,F#1,500 to fix his tyres after driving
OL,8,Fthrough pothole-ridden roads.
OL,10,FYoussef Zidouri damaged his wheels
OL,11,Fwhile driving near his home in Forest
OL,12,FFields in Nottingham. He has had to
OL,13,Fpay for a new set of wheels.
OL,15,FHe said: "On my main street, there's
OL,16,Fone just on a bend just as you turn
OL,17,Fand also on the main street.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1772283793
OL,3,CDriver left with #1,500 bill after
OL,4,Cpotholes damage wheels
OL,6,F"It's getting to the point where it's
OL,7,Fgetting a little bit dangerous,
OL,8,Fbecause instead of driving normally
OL,9,Fyou're looking ahead for what pothole
OL,10,FI can avoid."
OL,12,FWheel and tyre business Treadmark in
OL,13,FTrent Lane gets dozens of drivers like
OL,14,FMr Zidouri coming in every week with
OL,15,Fpothole-related damages.
OL,17,FOwner Shayne Demera says his workshop
OL,18,Fis having to do up to ten tyre
OL,19,Freplaements a day. He also gets called
OL,20,Fout for roadside repairs.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1772283793
OL,3,CDriver left with #1,500 bill after
OL,4,Cpotholes damage wheels
OL,6,FIt is estimated there are now around
OL,7,Fsix potholes per mile on our council-
OL,8,Fcontrolled roads, according to the RAC.
OL,10,FOn Thursday, Nottinghamshire County
OL,11,FCouncil announced an extra #2 million
OL,12,Fto road repairs at its full council
OL,13,Fmeeting.
OL,15,FBut Mr Demera believes filling up
OL,16,Fpotholes is not a long-term solution
OL,17,Fto the deteriorating state of the
OL,18,Fcounty's roads.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1772283793
OL,3,CDriver left with #1,500 bill after
OL,4,Cpotholes damage wheels
OL,6,FHe said: "I think they've got to be
OL,7,Ftaken up and started again. This
OL,8,Fpatching up work is not going to last,
OL,9,Fthere's too much moisture in the
OL,10,Froads. I'm not a road layer but I know
OL,11,Fenough that you can't just patch a
OL,12,Fhole up."
OL,14,FThere is growing anger at the state of
OL,15,Fthe roads in Nottinghamshire, with
OL,16,Freports that one man needed hospital
OL,17,Ftreatment after falling into a pothole.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
